SELECT id, 2,
  'intermediate',
  '2245 Heathermoor Drive — Revocable Trust Dissolution',
  'You are appraising a home at 2245 Heathermoor Drive, Greer SC for a revocable living trust dissolution and federal estate tax filing, on referral from Blue Ridge Trust & Estate Planning. Upon the grantor''s death, the revocable trust became irrevocable and its assets are included in the taxable estate. The retrospective effective date is the date of death, 16 months prior to today. The subject is a 2,100 SF home built in 2002 with three bedrooms, 2.5 bathrooms, and a 2-car garage, in good condition. Your role is to develop an independent opinion of Fair Market Value as defined by IRS Revenue Ruling 59-60, as of the date of death.

Three closed sales are provided. They differ from the subject across three adjustment types: GLA, bathrooms, and market conditions (one comparable sold 9 months before the date of death). Two analytical challenges are introduced at this level: a divergent GLA paired sale that must be identified and excluded with documented reasoning (an unexplained inconsistency in IRS-reviewed appraisal creates audit risk), and a market conditions adjustment derived from retrospective resale pairs — opposing counsel and the IRS will challenge any data that postdates the effective date. Identify the differing features, derive market-supported adjustment values, apply them, and reconcile the adjusted prices into your retrospective Fair Market Value opinion. The opinion supports the trust dissolution filing and will be included in the IRS Form 706 submission.'
FROM scenario_categories WHERE code = 'M2-S4-C3';

