2,250 SF", "C3": "2,250 SF"}, "feature_key": "gla", "diff_comps": ["C1"], "diff_directions": {"C1": "superior"}}, {"label": "Bathrooms", "subject": "3 full", "comp_values": {"C1": "3 full", "C2": "3 full", "C3": "3 full"}, "diff_comps": []}, {"label": "Garage", "subject": "2-car", "comp_values": {"C1": "2-car", "C2": "2-car", "C3": "2-car"}, "diff_comps": []}, {"label": "Year Built", "subject": "2010", "comp_values": {"C1": "2010", "C2": "2011", "C3": "2009"}, "diff_comps": []}, {"label": "Condition", "subject": "Good", "comp_values": {"C1": "Good", "C2": "Average", "C3": "Good"}, "feature_key": "cnd", "diff_comps": ["C2"], "diff_directions": {"C2": "inferior"}}, {"label": "Location", "subject": "Standard", "comp_values": {"C1": "Standard", "C2": "Standard", "C3": "Amenitied/Gated"}, "feature_key": "loc", "diff_comps": ["C3"], "diff_directions": {"C3": "superior"}}], "step2": {"tabs": [{"key": "paired", "label": "Paired Sales Analysis", "intro": "Use the supporting market data to derive contributory values. Four tables: GLA (with outlier Pair 4), location, condition, and market conditions. Three of four adjustment types have no cost method. The GLA Pair 4 outlier must be excluded with documented reasoning — the asset management client will scrutinize the inputs.", "tables": [{"kind": "paired_dollar_per_unit", "feature_key": "gla", "title": "GLA Pairs — Calculate $/SF", "instruction": "Current-market pairs confirmed equivalent except GLA. Divide Price Difference ÷ SF Difference. Pairs 1–3 cluster very tightly. Pair 4 produces a notably higher rate and must be excluded with documented reasoning rather than averaged.", "input_label": "Your $/SF", "input_suffix": "/SF", "rows": [{"label": "1", "cells": ["2,100 SF / $338,000", "2,250 SF / $344,550", "150 SF", "$6,550"]}, {"label": "2", "cells": ["2,150 SF / $344,000", "2,300 SF / $350,500", "150 SF", "$6,500"]}, {"label": "3", "cells": ["2,200 SF / $350,000", "2,350 SF / $356,650", "150 SF", "$6,650"]}, {"label": "4", "cells": ["2,050 SF / $332,000", "2,250 SF / $343,700", "200 SF", "$11,700"]}], "column_headers": ["Pair", "Sale A (SF / Price)", "Sale B (SF / Price)", "SF Diff", "Price Diff"], "concluded_label": "Concluded GLA Adjustment", "concluded_helper": "Bracket Pairs 1–3; exclude Pair 4 with documented reasoning."}, {"kind": "paired_dollar_diff", "feature_key": "loc", "title": "Location Pairs — Standard vs. Amenitied/Gated", "instruction": "No cost method available for location. Calculate price difference (Amenitied/Gated minus Standard). Pairs 1–3 cluster tightly; Pair 4 diverges modestly.", "input_label": "Your Price Difference", "input_suffix": "", "rows": [{"label": "1", "cells": ["$339,000", "$354,000"]}, {"label": "2", "cells": ["$346,500", "$361,500"]}, {"label": "3", "cells": ["$352,000", "$367,500"]}, {"label": "4", "cells": ["$334,000", "$350,700"]}], "column_headers": ["Pair", "Standard Sale", "Amenitied/Gated Sale"], "concluded_label": "Concluded Location Adjustment", "concluded_helper": "Bracket Pairs 1–3; address Pair 4."}, {"kind": "paired_dollar_diff", "feature_key": "cnd", "title": "Condition Pairs — Good vs. Average", "instruction": "No cost method available. Calculate price difference (Good minus Average). Three pairs cluster tightly.", "input_label": "Your Price Difference", "input_suffix": "", "rows": [{"label": "1", "cells": ["$342,000", "$354,000"]}, {"label": "2", "cells": ["$336,500", "$348,300"]}, {"label": "3", "cells": ["$348,000", "$360,200"]}], "column_headers": ["Pair", "Average Sale", "Good Sale"], "concluded_label": "Concluded Condition Adjustment", "concluded_helper": "Three pairs — tight bracket."}, {"kind": "paired_pct_per_month", "feature_key": "date", "title": "Market Conditions — Resale Pair Analysis", "instruction": "The same properties sold twice. For each pair, calculate the monthly appreciation rate using: (Resale − Original) ÷ Original ÷ Months × 100", "input_label": "Your %/Month", "input_suffix": "%/mo", "rows": [{"label": "A", "cells": ["$345,000", "$357,210", "10"]}, {"label": "B", "cells": ["$338,000", "$349,534", "11"]}, {"label": "C", "cells": ["$352,000", "$363,818", "10"]}], "column_headers": ["Property", "Original Sale Price", "Resale Price", "Months"], "concluded_label": "Concluded Monthly Rate", "concluded_helper": "Bracket your three results."}]}, {"key": "cost", "label": "Cost-Based Support", "intro": "Only GLA has an applicable cost method. Cost ($62.13/SF) is significantly above the consistent paired sales range ($43–$44/SF) — a large ceiling. For a 2010 property of this type, the market pays well below replacement cost for additional square footage. This gap is directly actionable information for the investor: the GLA contribution is a market-driven value, not a cost-driven one. Location, Condition, and Market Conditions are market-derived only.", "items": [{"kind": "cost_calc", "feature_key": "gla", "title": "GLA Contributory Value ($/SF)", "fact_rows": [["RCN", "$81.00 / SF"], ["Effective Age", "14 years"], ["Economic Life", "60 years"], ["Depreciation Rate", "14 ÷ 60 = 23.3%"], ["Formula", "$81.00 × (1 − 0.233) = ?"]], "input_suffix": "/SF"}]}], "reconciliation": {"instruction": "Review both method indications and enter your reconciled adjustment for each item. GLA cost significantly exceeds paired sales — a clear ceiling. Location, Condition, and Market Conditions reconcile from paired sales only. The large cost-vs-market gap for GLA warrants advisory commentary to the client.", "items": [{"feature_key": "gla", "label": "GLA Adjustment ($/SF)"}, {"feature_key": "loc", "label": "Location Adjustment ($)"}, {"feature_key": "cnd", "label": "Condition Adjustment ($)"}, {"feature_key": "date", "label": "Market Conditions Adjustment (%/mo)"}]}}, "step3": {"instruction": "Apply your reconciled adjustments to each comparable. Use NEGATIVE values for superior comps and POSITIVE for inferior. Comp 1 receives one negative GLA adjustment. Comp 2 receives one positive condition adjustment. Comp 3 receives two opposing-direction adjustments — Location is negative (amenitied/gated community is superior) and Market Conditions is positive (sold 10 months ago, inferior). For Comp 3 (market conditions), calculate as: $368,000 × 10 months × your reconciled %/mo ÷ 100. Each rationale should explain market-driven pricing intelligence to the investor — particularly the GLA cost-vs-market gap and Comp 3''s gross-vs-net adjustment story.", "applicable": {"C1": ["gla"], "C2": ["cnd"], "C3": ["loc", "date"]}, "method_dropdown": ["Paired Sales Analysis", "Location Paired Sales Analysis", "Market Conditions (Resale Pairs)", "Cost-Based Support", "Grouped Paired Sales", "Regression Analysis", "Appraiser Judgment / Extraction"], "support_min_chars": 15}, "step4": {"show_net_gross_panel": true}}'::jsonb,
  '{"step1_correct_flags": {"C1": ["gla"], "C2": ["cnd"], "C3": ["loc", "date"]}, "step1_rationale": "Comp 1 differs only in GLA — 150 SF larger than the subject (superior, single negative adjustment). Comp 2 differs only in condition — average versus the subject''s good (inferior, single positive adjustment). Comp 3 differs in two features with opposing directions: amenitied/gated location (superior, negative adjustment) and sold 10 months ago in an appreciating market (inferior date, positive adjustment). Bathrooms, garage, and year built are equivalent across all three comparables.", "step2_tables": {"paired": {"gla": {"pair_answers": [43.67, 43.33, 44.33, 58.5], "concluded_range": [43.0, 45.0], "rationale": "Pairs 1–3 cluster very tightly at $43.33–$44.33/SF — exceptionally consistent market support. Pair 4 produces $58.50/SF and must be excluded with documented reasoning (different submarket, anomalous transaction, or data anomaly). For a sophisticated asset management client, the explanation must be transparent: Pair 4 was investigated and excluded based on differing market characteristics."}, "loc": {"pair_answers": [15000, 15000, 15500, 16700], "concluded_range": [14800, 15700], "rationale": "Pairs 1–3 produce $15,000–$15,500 — tight market support for the location premium. Pair 4 ($16,700) is a modest outlier; address but do not weight heavily. Reconcile within Pairs 1–3."}, "cnd": {"pair_answers": [12000, 11800, 12200], "concluded_range": [11700, 12300], "rationale": "Three pairs produce $11,800, $12,000, and $12,200 — a tight $400 spread. Strong, consistent market support for the Good vs. Average condition increment."}, "date": {"pair_answers": [0.354, 0.31, 0.336], "concluded_range": [0.3, 0.37], "rationale": "Three resale pairs produce 0.31%, 0.34%, and 0.35%/mo. Tight support for monthly appreciation rate."}}, "cost": {"gla": {"answer": 62.13, "rationale": "$81.00 × (1 − 0.233) = $62.13/SF. Significantly above the consistent paired sales range of $43.33–$44.33/SF — a large ceiling, the largest cost-vs-market gap seen in Module 4. For a 2010 property of this type, the market pays well below replacement cost for additional square footage. This is directly actionable information for the investor: the GLA contribution is a market-driven value, not a cost-driven one — informing renovation decisions as well as pricing strategy."}}}, "step2_reconciliation": {"gla": {"range": [43.0, 45.0], "rationale": "Paired sales support $43.33–$44.33/SF (Pairs 1–3). Pair 4 ($58.50/SF) excluded with documented reasoning. Cost support of $62.13/SF is well above and acts only as a ceiling — the gap is the largest in Module 4 and warrants explicit advisory commentary that buyers consistently pay well below replacement cost for additional GLA at this 2010 vintage. Reconcile near $44/SF."}, "loc": {"range": [15000, 15500], "rationale": "Paired sales support $15,000–$15,500 (Pairs 1–3). Pair 4 ($16,700) addressed but not weighted. No cost method applicable. Reconcile near the midpoint at approximately $15,250."}, "cnd": {"range": [11800, 12200], "rationale": "Three pairs produce a tight $400 spread. No cost method applicable. Reconcile near $12,000."}, "date": {"range": [0.32, 0.35], "rationale": "Paired sales support 0.31–0.35%/mo. No cost method applicable. Reconcile near 0.335%/mo."}}, "step3_adjustments": {"C1": {"gla": {"direction": "negative", "amount_per_unit": -44.0, "units": 150, "computed_amount": -6600, "method": "Paired Sales Analysis", "rationale": "Comp 1 is 150 SF larger than the subject (superior). At reconciled $44/SF (Pairs 1–3; Pair 4 outlier excluded), the GLA adjustment is −$6,600. The cost-vs-market gap ($62.13/SF cost vs. $44/SF market) is informative for the investor: buyers in this market and vintage do not pay replacement cost for additional GLA — implications for both pricing strategy and any renovation decisions."}}, "C2": {"cnd": {"direction": "positive", "amount": 12000, "method": "Paired Sales Analysis", "rationale": "Comp 2 is in average condition versus the subject''s good condition (inferior). The condition increment from three tightly-clustered pairs is approximately $12,000 (midpoint of $11,800–$12,200). No cost method applicable for condition; market reaction governs."}}, "C3": {"loc": {"direction": "negative", "amount": -15250, "method": "Location Paired Sales Analysis", "rationale": "Comp 3 is in an amenitied/gated community (superior to the subject''s standard location). The location premium derived from three Pairs 1–3 is approximately $15,250 (midpoint of $15,000–$15,500). Pair 4 ($16,700) addressed but not weighted."}, "date": {"direction": "positive", "amount": 12328, "method": "Market Conditions (Resale Pairs)", "rationale": "Comp 3 sold 10 months ago in an appreciating market (inferior date). At reconciled 0.335%/mo: $368,000 × 10 × 0.335 ÷ 100 = $12,328. Three resale pairs support this rate, bringing Comp 3 in line with current market values. Comp 3''s opposing adjustments produce a small NET figure but a meaningful GROSS figure — reduce Comp 3''s weight in the final pricing recommendation."}}}, "step4_adjusted_prices": {"C1": {"unadjusted": 374000, "adjusted": 367400}, "C2": {"unadjusted": 346000, "adjusted": 358000}, "C3": {"unadjusted": 368000, "adjusted": 365078}}, "step4_reconciliation_narrative": "Adjusted prices range from approximately $358,000 to $367,400 — a spread of about $9,400. Comps 1 and 3 cluster at $365,000–$367,400, with Comp 2 at $358,000. Comps 1 and 2 — each requiring a single, cleanly-supported adjustment — are given primary weight. Comp 3''s opposing adjustments (Location −$15,250 and Market Conditions +$12,328) produce a small net figure of approximately −$2,900 but a substantial gross adjustment of approximately $27,600 (~7.5% gross). In a disposition advisory context, the investor should understand that while the net adjustment is small, the comparable required meaningful analytical work to bring it in line with current market conditions; Comp 3 receives REDUCED WEIGHT in the final pricing recommendation. The advisory opinion of current market value is supported in the $360,000–$367,000 range, anchored by Comps 1 and 2. The advanced-level teaching points are: (1) the GLA cost-vs-market gap ($62.13/SF vs. $44/SF) is the largest seen across Module 4 and is directly actionable for the investor — the market does not reward adding square footage at replacement cost, informing renovation as well as pricing strategy; (2) the GLA Pair 4 outlier exclusion must be transparently documented for a sophisticated asset management client; (3) the distinction between net and gross adjustment percentages — a small net figure does not mean minimal analytical burden, and weighting logic is what transforms a competent appraisal into a useful advisory opinion.", "tolerance_note": "Student answers are accepted within ±5% of model derived values for paired-sales calculations and within the indicated reconciliation range. Step 3 adjustments accepted within ±13% of the computed amount for GLA, ±12% for location and condition, and ±16% for market conditions."}'::jsonb
FROM scenarios s
JOIN scenario_categories sc ON sc.id = s.category_id
JOIN module_sections ms ON ms.id = sc.section_id
JOIN section_fields f ON f.section_id = ms.id AND f.field_key = 'adjustment_grid'
WHERE sc.code = 'M2-S4-C4'
  AND s.order_index = 3;

COMMIT;

